{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in clams. Remove bowl and cover clams with water and 2 tsp salt. Allow to soak for 20 minutes. Remove clams and rinse with clean water. Transfer clams to a colander and discard water.","Place garlic and olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté <nobr>5 min\/250°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add wine and ⅛ tsp salt. Place Varoma into position, place rinsed clams into Varoma dish, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>14 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma and transfer clams to a serving bowl. Pour sauce over clams and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["35 oz small littleneck clams, scrubbed and debearded","water, to soak clams","2 tsp salt              (optional)","2 garlic cloves","1 oz olive oil","5 ½ oz dry white wine","&frac18; tsp salt, optional (see Tip)","½ oz cilantro, chopped"]}],"id":"r213416","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-afyVWBa2B8s\/XZQvdt-Ax8I\/AAAAAAAAcck\/N4yW5ETgKkoAnWzbsewT8amw7gF9RMWXQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_GbKY4xQ_6oa_inbK.png","title":"Clams in White Wine with Cilantro","publishedAt":"2017-08-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.3 g","fat":"9.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"0.4 g","calories":"500 kJ \/ 120 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowl, colander, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Discard any clams that are open before cooking and do not open up after steaming.","Clams are often purged of sand and grit prior to being sold at supermarkets but still require rinsing before using. Wild clams or clams from smaller purveyors should always be purged. If clams require purging, omit ⅛ tsp salt from the sauce.","This recipe is suitable for up to 45 oz. of small littleneck clams."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","25m","4 portions"]}